# VS Queue Monitor — agent guidance (web branch)

Apply when editing **`app.js`**, **`README.md`**, **`docs/DESIGN.md`**, or related web sources. Complements **git-commit** (version bump in `app.js`, README, `npm run build`).

## Primary artifact

- This branch ships a **static web client** (`index.html` + `app.js` + `styles.css`, built to `dist/`). Assets under **`assets/`** are copied into `dist/` by the build. Do not assume a backend; all state is local to the browser unless explicitly documented otherwise.

## Queue position and “done” state

- **Position `0`** means the log shows **past connect-queue wait** (post-queue patterns on lines **after** the last queue-position line), not merely “position ≤ 1”. Map raw ≤1 + post-queue signal → `0` for KPI/graph.
- **Completion** (toast/sound), **Completed** status, **100% progress**, and celebration should align with **past-queue detection** / position `0`, not only hitting position `1` (long waits at `1` are normal).

## Log resolution and paths

- Prefer **strict** client-log discovery — do not fall back to arbitrary `*.log` files in a folder; that makes wrong folders look valid.
- **Browse** / pick flows follow browser security rules (File System Access API, secure origins). When the user cannot pick a path, recovery copy lives in README and in-app help — keep them aligned.

## Settings must match code

- **“Log every position change”**: When **off**, **omit** routine queue lines from History entirely — not just a different message. When **on**, log each transition.
- **Web (`app.js`):** Default **`logEveryChange`** is **true** unless configured otherwise.

## Interrupted mode

- While **Interrupted**, **freeze** KPI **Rate** / **Global Rate** display (e.g. snapshot at interrupt). Recency-weighted speed uses **wall time** and would otherwise drift every tick.

## Status strings (user-facing clarity)

- **Waiting for log file**: No readable log / no pick yet, as defined by the web client.
- **Warning: no queue detected**: Log is readable but tail has **no** connect-queue position line — not the same as “no file.”
- Distinguish **At front** (still in queue at `1`) vs **Completed** (position `0` / past-queue).

## ETA

- At **position `1`**, still show **EST. REMAINING** using a **one-step** model (and fallback when speed unknown), not `—`.

## Defaults

- Default **warning thresholds**: `10, 5, 1` (same idea as `DEFAULT_ALERT_THRESHOLDS` in design docs).

## README and DESIGN

- When behavior, paths, settings, or status text changes in ways users rely on, **update README in the same change set** (see **git-commit** rule).
- When **product intent**, **user journey**, or **UX principles** change, update **`docs/DESIGN.md`** in the same change set when those docs would otherwise drift.
